    "narrative": "Today\u2019s offensive outlook for Ghost Ride the WHIP centers on exploiting high-xERA matchups, headlined by **Jose Caballero** and **Mickey Moniak**. **Jose Caballero** (77.16) is our premier play; while his #8 spot in the lineup typically dampens expectations, he faces a soft matchup against Springs (4.60 xERA) and draws a massive +13% platoon boost. Crucially, we are counting on his elite speed against a slow-working starter to manufacture value in our scarcest category, Stolen Bases. Similarly, **Mickey Moniak** (75.97) leverages a high-ceiling matchup against V\u00e1squez (5.43 xERA). With an assumed #3 spot and a +14% dynamic platoon advantage, **Mickey Moniak** is positioned for a high-efficiency performance despite the neutral park factors. **Giancarlo Stanton** (67.71) rounds out our top-tier targets, benefiting from the same favorable matchup against Springs to capitalize on his power profile.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involved **Vinnie Pasquantino** (51.61) and **Zach McKinstry** (49.64). **Vinnie Pasquantino** narrowly held his spot in the UTIL slot over the fringe bench options, with his projection buoyed by a +5% wind-out factor that offsets a significant platoon penalty against the lefty Kay. While **Zach McKinstry** remains a marginal start, he serves as our primary contact-based stabilizer against Abel. We are monitoring **Gabriel Moreno** and **Corbin Carroll** closely; both are currently \"Lineup Pending,\" and their scores (43.46 and 56.10, respectively) are heavily suppressed by the elite 3.04 xERA of McLean. Should **Gabriel Moreno** be scratched or moved down the order, we will have to pivot, as he is currently operating barely above our efficiency floor. We remain without production from key depth pieces like **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Josh Naylor**, **James Wood**, and **Trevor Story**, who are all currently inactive, further emphasizing the need for **Max Muncy** (61.96) to provide steady production in the middle infield while our core stars await better pitching conditions.",
